-- Regions Financial Could Sell Morgan Keegan Unit, WSJ Reports
-- B y   C h r i s   S p i l l a n e
-- 2012-01-07T10:11:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-07/regions-financial-could-sell-morgan-keegan-unit-wsj-reports.html
Regions Financial Corp. (RF)  may sell its
Morgan Keegan & Co. unit to  Raymond James Financial Inc. (RJF)  or
 Stifel Financial Corp. (SF)  for as much as $1 billion, the Wall
Street Journal reported, citing unidentified people familiar
with the matter.  The sale may fetch between $900 million and $1 billion and
may be completed next week, the Journal said. J.P. Morgan Chase
& Co. will extend a line of credit of about $900 million to help
conclude the transaction, the newspaper said, citing other
unidentified people.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christopher Spillane in London at 
 cspillane3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at 
 ablackman@bloomberg.net  